snippet: Darryl Kelly, who was hired to clean out the photographer Harry Shunk’s apartment after his death and rescued about 2,000 items thrown into a dumpster, has auctioned off the last of the collection.
abstract: Darryl Kelly, who was hired to clean out photographer Harry Shunk’s Bronx apartment after his death and ended up rescuing about 2,000 objects of art thrown into a dumpster, has auctioned off the last of the collection; Kelly, subject of an August 12 Metropolitan section story, earned over $225,000 from his find.
lead_paragraph: Darryl Kelly, who was hired to clean out the photographer Harry Shunk’s apartment after his death and rescued about 2,000 items thrown into a dumpster, has auctioned off the last of the collection.

headline.seo: Cleanup Artist Reaps a Windfall With Harry Shunk’s Possessions
headline.main: Cleanup Artist’s Dumpster Trove Pays Off. A Lot.
